summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeVeganSet makeup for up to 16 hours of wear and minimize shine for up to 24 hours with Morphe's Bake & Set Setting Powder. This talc-free, lightweight, finely milled, silky loose powder sweeps on with an imperceptible, soft, natural finish, while smoothing pores and fine lines.
details: DetailsFeaturesTalc-free, lightweight, finely milled, silky loose powderTranslucent shade gives a sheer, soft-focus finishSmooths pores & fine linesDoes not crease or cakeAvailable in mini, regular, & jumbo sizes for on-the-go or everyday artistryPackaging may varyResearch ResultsSets makeup for up to 16 hours of wear*Minimizes shine for up to 24 hours*96% agreed it improved the wear & appearance of makeup*96% agreed it absorbed excess oil*100% agreed it is lightweight, comfortable to wear & invisible upon application*100% agreed it was smoothing*93% agreed it reduced appearance of pores & fine lines*90% agreed it did not crease or cake**Based on a clinical study of 32 subjects when worn with foundation vs. when wearing foundation aloneItem 2621391How To UseTo set, apply the powder with a powder brush by tapping off excess, and then sweeping powder over the complexion. To bake, apply powder with a puff or damp beauty sponge by gently pressing and rolling onto the complexion.IngredientsTranslucent: Mica, Aluminum Starch Octenylsuccinate, Silica, Lauroyl Lysine, Boron Nitride, Dimethicone/Vinyl Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Tocopheryl Acetate, Isoceteth-10, Caprylyl Glycol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Phenoxyethanol. May Contain: Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Red 40 Lake (CI 16035), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140).
how_to_use: To set, apply the powder with a powder brush by tapping off excess, and then sweeping powder over the complexion. To bake, apply powder with a puff or damp beauty sponge by gently pressing and rolling onto the complexion.

faceoff_positive.comments: I had never heard of Morphe before I started shopping for my beauty stuff exclusively at Ulta (used to be a Seph0ra disciple but Ulta has a much better rewards program, and a much broader variety of product and price points). I am finding that everything I've tried from the brand, from brushes to makeup, has been amazing. Their Fluidity concealer is my HG forever, I will only use their brushes now, and I'm here to re-purchase this powder. I mainly like it because it is talc-free but still does an excellent job of setting makeup, unlike the dozen or so other talc-free setting powders I've tried (including Fenty, ELF, NYX, Becca, Halo, CoverFX, etc.). I'm trying to avoid talc, at least in loose powders, since it is a known carcinogen and I've been inhaling setting powder every day of my life for the past 30-ish years! Anyway, so this powder. I will say that it really doesn't control oil much at all, but that's the trade-off for not containing talc. I can live with the more frequent blotting (I have super-oily skin). I bake everywhere that I use concealer (which ends up being nearly all of my face) with this, and it does not settle into lines, which is nothing short of miraculous. I am 45 and have large pores and very textured skin, along with a few wrinkles, and this keeps everything in place for 16+ hours without caking, breaking up, sliding, or disappearing. I often swim with a full face and come out with everything still mostly in place (another testament to the Fluidity concealer!) The finish is a soft matte rather than full matte, which I like because it looks more natural. Sorry this is so long, but I hope it helps others make a decision. This really is the best talc-free powder I've found, aside from Onomie, which I loved but the company seems to be out of business. So, given the price point, you have little to lose by giving this a shot. I'm so glad I did!
faceoff_positive.headline: 4.5 stars

faceoff_negative.comments:
I wanted to love this since it is specifically marketed as a "BAKE & SET" product. But if you have combo or even remotely dry skin, this powder will latch onto your dry patches and make them extremely more visible. It's also not the smoothest powder -- for example, the Tarte Smooth Operator and the Urban Decay Velvetizer are very, very finely milled and you can feel that in the application; they're very silky. This Morphe powder isn't silky to the touch, part of the reason I dislike it. But the main disappointment is due to it accentuating dry skin and settled into fine lines. Every time I set my concealer with this, it left a white cast and within 15 minutes you could see my concealer had separated and creased as if it had never been set with a powder. /: My purchase was in the shade "Brightening Pink," and it is fairly pigmented -- enough to brighten up wherever you place it, however as I mentioned, it doesn't work for me and my under eye area. It's decent to brighten up the center of the forehead, chin, and bridge of the nose for a nice brightening effect without having to use a shimmer highlight. BUT, again, if you have dry patches or blemishes on any of those areas as well, this powder is going to latch on to them and not blend out. I'd only use this on clients with extremely oily skin, but even then, there's better options out there. Shoot, even the E.L.F HD Powder performs better with a silkier texture. Sorry, Morphe. I still love you. 
xoxo,
Gossip Girl
